FBIS4-58009 "drlat104_b_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-104 Daily Report 27 May 1994 Dominican Republic Fuel Smuggling Accidents Leave 19 Dead Fuel Smuggling Accidents Leave 19 Dead PA2705183294 Paris AFP in Spanish 1659 GMT 27 May 94 PA2705183294 Paris AFP Spanish BFN [Text] Santo Domingo, 27 May (AFP) -- Armed Forces spokesmen report that 19 people have died and 42 others have been injured along the Dominican-Haitian border since the embargo on Haiti began to be intensified on Saturday. Citing military sources, local newspapers reported today that fatalities and injuries along the border have been caused by accidents involving vehicles that were smuggling fuel into Haiti and that were attempting to evade pusuing military vehicles. Over the weekend, the Dominican Army intensified its surveillance of more than 300 km of border with Haiti to prevent the smuggling of fuel into the neighboring country.
